<DOCNO> NYT19991010.0021 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-10 00:54 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2299 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s BC-BBN-DBACKS-MANTEI-AZR     10-10 0602
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DBACKS-MANTEI-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MANTEI `READY FOR NEXT SEA SON'  
 CLOSER WON'T DWELL ON LOSS IN 10TH INNING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By RICHARD OBERT  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ This was where Matt Mantei wanted to be and why the
Diamondbacks went after him in July: With the ball, do or die, the
Diamondbacks' season rested on Mantei's 98 mph fastball.
</P>
<P>
   Then Mantei's world froze as he watched center fielder Steve
Finley leap at the wall. He watched the ball descend. Into Finley's
glove, he prayed.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought he caught it at first,'' Mantei said. ``But then I
saw him bang up against the wall, so I knew it was over.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's over now. I'm ready for next season.''
</P>
<P>
   Mantei, who had saved so many games in helping turn the season
around, couldn't win this time. Unlikely hero Todd Pratt sent
Mantei's fastball over the center-field fence in the bottom of the
10th inning Saturday to send the New York Mets to the National
League Championship Series.
</P>
<P>
   Mantei says he won't let it devour him. He refused to replay it
in his mind, to dwell on defeat.
</P>
<P>
   ``All good things come to an end, eventually,'' Mantei said.
``We've got to keep our heads up.''
</P>
<P>
   Mantei was outstanding in rescuing the Diamondbacks from a
first-and-third, one-out situation in the eighth inning, then left
a runner stranded in the ninth before returning for the 10th. It's
the longest he's pitched since he went 2 innings in a July 24, 1998
game with the Florida Marlins.
</P>
<P>
   ``I still had a lot left in me,'' Mantei said. ``I felt great
going back out there. I felt real confident. He just beat me.''
</P>
<P>
   Left-hander Randy Johnson, who was hoping to have the ball one
last time in this series today, said he was proud of Mantei's
effort.
</P>
<P>
   ``His job normally is to go out there for one inning,'' Johnson
said. ``He gave it all he had. He twice left it in the position
where we were still tied. He didn't lose it.''
</P>
<P>
   Manager Buck Showalter said he felt he could go longer than
normal with a well-rested Mantei, who had not pitched in the series
before entering Game 4 in the eighth with the score tied.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mantei did a great job,'' Showalter said.
</P>
<P>
   But Mantei would gladly take a pitch or two back.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was hoping to drop a breaking ball for a strike,'' Mantei
said. ``Then, I threw a fastball right down the middle of the
plate. I think it was the first hit (Pratt) got in the series. What
a great time for it.''
</P>
<P>
   Finley stared at an empty glove with disbelief as fireworks shot
off behind him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't even hear them,'' Finley said.
</P>
<P>
   Finley was in the World Series last year with San Diego and said
he felt this team had what it takes to get there, especially after
acquiring Mantei from the Marlins on July 9.
</P>
<P>
   ``I still feel that way,'' Finley said. ``We just didn't get the
breaks.''
</P>
<P>
   He looked back at the play at the plate in the eighth inning
when second baseman Jay Bell, who had given the Diamondbacks a 3-2
lead with a two-run double, was called out on left fielder Melvin
Mora's throw to Pratt.
</P>
<P>
   Then he recalled the ball that escaped his glove, a glove that
has been so golden.
</P>
<P>
   ``It ends so quickly,'' Finley said. ``We had a lot of losses
like that, where we walked off the field.''
</P>
<P>
   It started on opening day in April, when the Los Angeles Dodgers
beat them with the long ball.
</P>
<P>
   And it ends here, on another long ball. There's no sense of
disgrace. Only agony.
</P>
<P>
   ``That pulled us together,'' Finley said about the opening
week's run of heart-breaking, last-inning losses. ``This will keep
us together.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-10-99 0054EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
