<SLUG> BC-FBC-ARIZONA-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC RECEIVER HOSPITALIZED 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By NORM FRAUENHEIM  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TUCSON _ Southern California wide receiver  &UR; R. Jay Soward was
knocked unconscious during a kickoff early in the fourth quarter of
Arizona's 31-22 victory Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   He tried to enter the game a few plays later but was pulled from
the field by the USC coaching staff. He was taken to a Tucson
hospital, where he underwent a CAT scan. The Trojans were planning
for him to stay at the hospital overnight as a precaution.
</P>
<P>
   On a roll &QL; 
 &UR; Trung Canidate's 194 rushing yards are the second-highest total in
his Arizona career. The senior from Central High was at his best
last year against Arizona State with 288 yards. While at Arizona,
he has rushed for more than 100 yards 12 times.
</P>
<P>
   SACK 'EM: The Wildcats' seven sacks against USC equaled their
total for the season before kickoff. &QL; 
Among the best &QL; 
USC coach  &UR; Paul Hackett on Arizona receiver  &UR; Dennis Northcutt: ``He
is a game-turner, one of the best.''
</P>
<P>
   The best &QL; 
Arizona quarterback  &UR; Keith Smith says Northcutt has no rivals. ``I
keep hearing about Florida State's  &UR; Peter Warrick,'' Smith said of
the Seminoles receiver who was suspended last week after he was
charged with felony theft. ``But I'm convinced that Dennis is the
best receiver in the country right now.''
</P>
<P>
   Could be the best &QL; 
Smith also has no doubts about Northcutt's ability as a defensive
back, a position he also played against USC. ``In practice, I'm
scared to death every time I have to try to throw against him,''
Smith said. ``I'm glad he's on my side.'' &QL; 
Some leadership &QL; 
In a departure from prior seasons, Arizona has picked captains for
the rest of the season. On offense, they are Smith and Northcutt.
On defense, they are linebackers  &UR; DaShon Polk and  &UR; Marcus Bell. The
Wildcats had been selecting captains on a game-by-game basis.
Leadership has been a question this year. &QL; 
For the defense &QL; 
Arizona's defense didn't play like the one that was ranked last in
the Pac-10 Conference against the rush. ``That did not look like a
defense that gives up 5 yards a rush,'' Hackett said. ``I am going
to have to look at the films to see what went wrong. That was a
totally different run defense than what we had seen before.'' &QL; 
Briefly &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Coach  &UR; Dick Tomey was in Auburn, Calif., Friday to attend
memorial services for former Wildcats linebacker  &UR; Akil Jackson, who
died Tuesday from an allergic reaction. Jackson, 27, was a starter
in 1993 and 1994, Desert Swarm days.
</P>
<P>
   Ex-Arizona Coach  &UR; Jim Young was honored Saturday at halftime for
his induction to the College Hall of Fame. Young, also a former
Purdue and Army coach, was at Arizona for three years in the mid
1970s.
</P>
<P>
   In 1973, he coached the Wildcats to a Western Athletic
Conference title. Other inductees are former San Diego State Coach
 &UR; Don Coryell, former Eastern Kentucky defensive back  &UR; George Floyd
and ex-Tennessee linebacker  &UR; Steve Kiner. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
