<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-SIDEBAR-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PAUS GETS THE JOB DONE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GERRY GITTELSON  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA _ Cory Paus doesn't want to hear about what he (begin
ital)can(end ital) do, or what he (begin ital)might(end ital) do.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, he just (begin ital)did(end ital) it.
</P>
<P>
   The UCLA freshman quarterback, ever earful of the constant
comparisons to a young Cade McNown, passed for 332 yards and two
touchdowns to carry the Bruins to a 34-29 Pac-10 football victory
over Oregon on Saturday night before 55,674 at the Rose Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Paus completed 21 of 34 passes with two interceptions.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought I played all right,'' he said. ``I had a few
mistakes, but as soon as I cut down on those mistakes, everything
is going to be OK.''
</P>
<P>
   As the Bruins snapped a two-game losing streak, and with Paus
gaining more and more confidence, there is definitely a good vibe
in Westwood.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've been saying all along Cory reminds me of Cade McNown, and
now he's progressing very well,'' UCLA coach Bob Toledo said. ``I'm
pleased because he's throwing the ball so well, and I know Cory
will keep on improving.''
</P>
<P>
   Paus completed 3 of 4 for 34 yards on UCLA's first scoring
drive, culminating in Chris Griffith's 47-yard field goal.
</P>
<P>
   Following an Oregon field goal that gave the Ducks a 7-3 lead,
Paus led UCLA on a 31-point spree this way:
</P>
<P>
   _His 31-yard pass to Danny Farmer set up Griffith's second field
goal, a 48-yarder cutting the gap to 10-6.
</P>
<P>
   _Two series later, he hit Farmer on a 11-yard TD with 38 seconds
remaining in the quarter to give UCLA a 20-10 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
   _He connected with Farmer on a 48-yard deep post on the first
play of the second half, then hit Bryan Fletcher for 9 yards. Brown
scored on a 10-yard run three plays later.
</P>
<P>
   _Ahead by 17 points, he came through again, this time on a
65-yard touchdown pass to Farmer that started with him rolling
left, then firing a bomb across field.
</P>
<P>
   Paus' performance proved he has fully recovered from bruised
ribs suffered in his first start against Fresno State on Sept. 18.
He returned against Arizona State last week _ completing 15 of 40
for 235 yards and one touchdown.
</P>
<P>
   However, he was still in pain and frequently rushed his passes
to avoid getting hit.
</P>
<P>
   On the day he was injured in his first start against Fresno
State, Paus had shown flashes of excellence. He completed his first
eight passes and was 9 for 12 for 113 yards and one touchdown.
</P>
<P>
   Paus has 905 yards passing, completing 52 percent, to go with
five TDs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
