<P>
   RELIGION _ If Gov. George W. Bush is trying to attract Catholic
and Jewish voters, talking about religion isn't likely to woo too
many of them. According to Catholic and Jewish theologians,
followers of those faiths often are put off by politicians' talk
about faith and religion. That's because the talk generally sounds
like evangelical Protestant faith. (Elizondo, Austin
American-Statesman). 30.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   PRESIDENTS _ A list of the country's past presidents and their
faiths. (Austin American-Statesman). 10.
