<P>
   OCEAN-ROCKET-LAUNCH (Los Angeles) _ Ushering in a new era in
rocketry, a multinational company has launched a communications
satellite into space from a platform floating in the Pacific Ocean,
the first such launch from sea rather than from land. By Andrew
Pollack.
</P>
<P>
   NAVAJO-CODE-WARRIORS (Gallup, N.M.) _ During World War II,
hundreds of Navajos were sent to the Pacific on a mission, to use
their language to create secret codes the Japanese could not break.
They did and they kept their mission secret for many years. This
weekend some of the Navajo veterans are reuniting to tell their
stories at a reservation in Gallup. By Todd S. Purdum. (With a map)
</P>
<P>
   WYO-GAYMURDER-TRIAL (Laramie, Wyo.) _ Curtain raiser on the
trial of the second man accused of the brutal murder of a gay
college student, Matthew Shepard. The trial begins on Tuesday. By
Michael Janofsky.
</P>
<P>
   TENTATIVE: These three stories will be held if they do not make
Page One.
</P>
<P>
   D.C.-HIGHTECH-BOOM (Washington) _ The Washington region is
undergoing a profound cultural, economic and social change as
outside-the-beltway technology takes over the leading role that
used to be held by government agencies. By at least one measure,
the area is now the tech capital of the nation. By Joel Brinkley.
(With photo and map.)
</P>
<P>
   ELITE-SCHOOLS-MINORITIES (Los Angeles) _ Recent studies suggest
that education at elite universities like Smith has become the
backbone of the black and Hispanic middle class, but administrators
at such schools have largely hit a wall in efforts to lure more
minorities. ``It's a struggle,'' said Gregory S. Prince Jr.,
president of Hampshire College and head of a five-college coalition
in Western Massachusetts that includes Smith. By Jodi Wilgoren.
</P>
<P>
   MENTALLY-ILL-VOTERS (Undated) _ A new group called the Mental
Health Voter Empowerment Project is mounting a campaign to create a
nationwide constituency of people with mental illness by locating
potential voters, registering them to vote, educating them about
mental health issues and making sure they get to the polls on
election day. By Erica Goode. (Will move in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS &LR;  (Moving in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
