<SLUG> BC-BOND-CALENDAR-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CREDIT OFFERINGS SCHEDULED FOR THIS WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Tuesday's auction of three- and six-month bills and a 52-week bill
being auctioned on Wednesday. Monday is a federal holiday and there
is no trading in U.S. Treasury securities and no trading of futures
on the Chicago Board of Trade, which is closed for observance of
Columbus Day.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 4.66 percent
and a six-month bill was 4.88 percent. The rate for the 52-week
bill was 5.02 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
